 govt sits helpless|date=2020-02-08|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-02-14}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n\nThe film was scheduled to be released on 21 February 2020, however, it was banned in Punjab by Capt. [[Amarinder Singh]], [[Chief Minister of Punjab (India)|Chief Minister of Punjab]] for promoting violence.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/punjab-bans-movie-shooter-for-promoting-violence/article30776649.ece|title=Punjab bans movie \u2018Shooter\u2019 for \u2018promoting violence\u2019|date=2020-02-10|work=[[The Hindu]]|access-date=2020-02-15|others=Special Correspondent|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Banning the film got divided opinions from [[Punjabi cinema]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/a-censor-board-for-punjabi-films-42370|title=A censor board for Punjabi films?|last=Kaur|first=Gurnaaz|date=16 February 2020|website=The Tribune|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Shooter\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = Jass Manak, Guri, Veet Baljit and Jagpal Sandhu\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| released   = \n| recorded   = \n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = \n| label      = Geet MP3\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc = \n| audio1 = \n}}\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline = Track listing\n| total_length = \n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Shoot Da Order\n| extra1 = Jass Manak, Jagpal Sandhu\n| length1 = 3:25\n| title2 = Maa\n| extra2 = Veet Baljit\n| length2 = 1:50\n| title3 = Gal Sun\n| extra3 = Jass Manak\n| length3 = 3:06\n| title4 = Hitler\n| extra4 = Guri\n| length4 = 3:42\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n==External links==\n\n{{Punjabi-film-stub}}[https://fantasiabarrinoofficial.com/2020/04/01/shooter-punjabi-movie-download-leaked-hd/ Shooter Punjabi Movie]\n[[Category:Punjabi-language films]] \n[[Category:2020 films]] \n[[Category:2020s Punjabi-language films]] \n[[Category:Indian films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Punjabi-language action film}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Shooter\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = Dilsher Singh<br />Khushpal Singh\n| writer         = \n| based_on       = \n| starring       = Jayy Randhawa<br />Swalina<br />Vada Grewal\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| studio         = <br>GK Digital\n| distributor    = \n| runtime        = \n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Punjabi<!--primary release language only-->\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Shooter''''',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/punjabi/movies/previews/shooter/articleshow/73439367.cms|title=\u2018Shooter\u2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-02-14}}</ref> originally titled as '''''Sukha Kahlon'''''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/cm-capt-amarinder-singh-bans-punjabi-film-shooter-for-promoting-violence-and-crime-1644699-2020-02-09|title=CM Capt Amarinder Singh bans Punjabi film Shooter for promoting violence and crime|date=February 9, 2020|website=[[India Today]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-15}}</ref> is an upcoming Indian [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]-language [[action film]] directed by Dilsher Singh and Khushpal Singh.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/punjabi/movies/news/shooter-the-trailer-of-jayy-randhawas-debut-punjabi-movie-is-out/articleshow/73419751.cms|title=\u2018Shooter\u2019: The trailer of Jayy Randhawa\u2019s debut Punjabi movie is out - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-02-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/movie-glorifying-slain-gangster-set-for-release-govt-sits-helpless/story-rdoRHW